						<summary>

						<p>On a stone built into the platform of the <hi rend="italic">dhvajastambha</hi> in the Hanumān temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1455, Vijaya, Mārgaśira, śu. 10, Wednesday, corresponding to 1533 A.D., November 26.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of the Garuḍa-pillar to the god Hanumantadēva by Malla[ya], son of Nallaballi Malli-Reḍḍi.</p>						

